The paper deals with achieving information theoretic location privacy in database-driven cognitive radio networks (CRNs) using multi-server private information retrieval (PIR). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as the paper deals with privacy and information theory in the context of network architecture. Additionally, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible categories as the paper discusses the use of multiple servers and database-driven CRNs.
